<subSubSection id="E4A88E989038C2BBBF02FB369B568153" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8E849915BD1933D7E4789681135A8772" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E5086C086C39C740AFCF9044F4670D89" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<bibRefCitation id="04949FEC91183FABE6FF815188CDC182" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.954.49738" author="Li, TT" journalOrPublisher="Zookeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="31 - 46" refId="B28" refString="Li, TT, Liu, DX, Qiu, DY, Yue, QY, 2020. Two new species of Episymploce Bey-Bienko, 1950 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) from China. Zookeys 954: 31 - 46, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.954.49738" title="Two new species of Episymploce Bey-Bienko, 1950 (Blattodea, Ectobiidae, Blattellinae) from China." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.954.49738" volume="954" year="2020">Li et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
established 
<taxonomicName id="E06D452FDC38E18FF4D3E34A152B87F6" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce maxima" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="ACF6ECAAF8E2F89708243AA5E8A7925D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we transfer this species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1FAC42B822C8E3BCE9C2E610CE349FB4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Symploce maxima (Li et al, 2020) comb. nov., male: A, B Duwei County, Guizhou: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C, D Leishan County, Guizhou: C dorsal view; D ventral view; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A-D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690403" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">3</figureCitation>
) to 
<taxonomicName id="2D3FC4817C9F6E77454B55640A4EE888" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCD25022543DAF66D19ECF02E45A68C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the following reasons: 1) in morphology, body size large (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="847B4800768C176D89F6F9FA5098EF0B" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Symploce maxima (Li et al, 2020) comb. nov., male: A, B Duwei County, Guizhou: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C, D Leishan County, Guizhou: C dorsal view; D ventral view; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A-D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690403" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">3A-D</figureCitation>
), T9 unspecialized, and no incrassate or crimping on the posterior margin of the subgenital plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0EB56DEED880D5714B3978F4199BF3F3" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Symploce maxima (Li et al, 2020) comb. nov., male: A, B Duwei County, Guizhou: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C, D Leishan County, Guizhou: C dorsal view; D ventral view; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A-D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690403" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">3N</figureCitation>
); 2) in phylogenetic analysis, 
<taxonomicName id="0A323A727CE175C4DFFFC07E600BA9C6" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce maxima" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maxima">
<emphasis id="0066C038A82BD3E5756947EF5B5A099A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce maxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li, Liu, Qiu and Yue was placed as the sister of 
<taxonomicName id="94732F63C4E02EFEFC6D6F7E47492676" authorityName="Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce sphaerica" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphaerica">
<emphasis id="695189C86675065B754304C29C274CA0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce sphaerica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a high support value (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="78F917702A90416EE1458D936E35CFD2" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on three mitochondrial genes 12 S rRNA, 16 S rRNA, COII and two nuclear genes 28 S rRNA, histone H 3. The topologies yielded by Bayesian inference (BI) are almost identical with ML tree (see supplementary material Fig. S 1). Branch labels provide bootstrap support (bs) of nodes in ML and posterior probability (pp) (%) of nodes in BI; (*) indicates the branch label of the corresponding analysis is 100 or 1.0, respectively; (-) means the node is absent for the given analysis." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690401" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">1</figureCitation>
, supplementary material Fig. S1), forming a clade together with other 
<taxonomicName id="A84F4AEB14922BEFCC9E8432AEEBFC92" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2BC48D71267EA9F51D93DCD7F234BF90" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. In addition, different individuals of this species exhibit some variations in body color, especially on the pronotum: the sample from Duwei County are black brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0525FAC3AF7926E668BC3C3D6C7FFEC9" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Symploce maxima (Li et al, 2020) comb. nov., male: A, B Duwei County, Guizhou: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C, D Leishan County, Guizhou: C dorsal view; D ventral view; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A-D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690403" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">3A, B</figureCitation>
), others from Leishan County are yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4523E4AEAC926267289CCB2C8A8FEEC9" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Symploce maxima (Li et al, 2020) comb. nov., male: A, B Duwei County, Guizhou: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C, D Leishan County, Guizhou: C dorsal view; D ventral view; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A-D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690403" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">3C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
